AB  - In panel data analysis, it is important to identify subgroups of units with heterogeneous parameters. This can not only increase the model flexibility but also produce more efficient estimation by pooling information across units within the same group. In this paper, we propose a new quantile-regression-based clustering method for panel data. We develop an iterative algorithm using a similar idea of k-means clustering to identify subgroups with heterogeneous slopes at a single quantile level or across multiple quantiles. The asymptotic properties of the group membership estimator and corresponding group-specific slope estimator are established. The finite sample performance of the proposed method is assessed through simulation and the analysis of an economic growth data.
